() Tj
T*
(This project is an AI-Powered CV Screening and Job Match Platform built with an ASP.NET) Tj
T*
(backend and a React frontend. The purpose of the system is to help recruiters upload a job) Tj
T*
(description, submit multiple CVs, automatically analyze candidates, rank them against the) Tj
T*
(role, and explain the reasons behind the ranking.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Simple Interview Script) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Problem Statement) Tj
T*
(I built this project to solve a common recruiting problem. Recruiters often spend a lot of) Tj
T*
(time manually reviewing large numbers of resumes, and that process can be slow,) Tj
T*
(inconsistent, and difficult to scale. My project automates that workflow by allowing) Tj
T*
(recruiters to upload a job description and multiple CVs, then automatically score and rank) Tj
T*
(the candidates.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Frontend Explanation) Tj
T*
(The frontend is built with React and provides a simple recruiter workflow. First, the) Tj
T*
(recruiter logs into the system. Then they provide a job description either by uploading a) Tj
T*
(file or pasting the text directly. After that, they upload multiple candidate CVs in one) Tj
T*
(batch. Once screening starts, the UI shows progress stages such as file upload, parsing,) Tj
T*
(scoring, and ranking. Finally, the results page displays ranked candidates, match) Tj
T*
(percentages, strengths, gaps, and explanations.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(I designed the frontend to stay simple and professional. Instead of overwhelming the user) Tj
T*
(with too many controls, I focused on a clear step-by-step flow: provide the job description,) Tj
T*
(upload CVs, run screening, and review ranked results.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key frontend points:) Tj
T*
(React was used to build reusable UI components.) Tj
T*
(State management is handled through React hooks.) Tj
T*
(The UI supports authentication, upload forms, progress feedback, ranking results, and reset) Tj
T*
(behavior.) Tj
T*
(The navbar navigation scrolls users to the correct sections.) Tj
T*
(The interface is restricted so recruiters must log in before using the main workflow.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Backend Explanation) Tj
T*
(The backend is built with ASP.NET Core as a Web API. It handles authentication, file) Tj
T*
(uploads, CV parsing, candidate evaluation, and ranking generation. The backend exposes) Tj
T*
(endpoints for sign-up, login, logout, screening requests, and ranking report retrieval. I) Tj
T*
